

1
00:00:12.046 --> 00:00:12.956 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Hi everybody.

2
00:00:13.206 --> 00:00:14.886 A:middle
I'm Chris Espinosa from Apple.

3
00:00:15.196 --> 00:00:16.406 A:middle
We're going to have
a lot of fun today.

4
00:00:16.406 --> 00:00:18.476 A:middle
We're talking about
kids and apps.

5
00:00:18.976 --> 00:00:22.186 A:middle
Going to cover a few things,
going to talk about the history

6
00:00:22.186 --> 00:00:24.856 A:middle
of Apple and kids, how
we got where we are.

7
00:00:25.396 --> 00:00:28.306 A:middle
Some recent regulatory
activity worldwide

8
00:00:28.306 --> 00:00:30.116 A:middle
and in the U.S. that's
going to affect you

9
00:00:30.116 --> 00:00:32.966 A:middle
if you're vending apps
that are addressed to kids;

10
00:00:33.446 --> 00:00:38.036 A:middle
some new programs we've had
in the last year for Apple IDs

11
00:00:38.036 --> 00:00:41.486 A:middle
for kids under 13, both the
Student Apple ID program

12
00:00:41.486 --> 00:00:43.726 A:middle
and Family Sharing that
was introduced on Monday;

13
00:00:44.096 --> 00:00:47.256 A:middle
talk about your responsibilities
if you're selling apps

14
00:00:47.316 --> 00:00:51.086 A:middle
that are directed at kids; some
best practices for doing that;

15
00:00:51.356 --> 00:00:54.066 A:middle
and then a brief view about what
to do about other countries.

16
00:00:55.046 --> 00:00:57.196 A:middle
But first of all
a little history:

17
00:00:57.576 --> 00:00:59.736 A:middle
Apple and kids go way back.

18
00:01:00.056 --> 00:01:02.116 A:middle
I personally know this,
because I was a kid

19
00:01:02.116 --> 00:01:06.486 A:middle
when I started working at
Apple on the Apple II in 1977.

20
00:01:06.566 --> 00:01:09.916 A:middle
One of our first programs
was called Kids Can't Wait.

21
00:01:10.086 --> 00:01:13.316 A:middle
We've been getting
computers in front of kids

22
00:01:13.516 --> 00:01:17.636 A:middle
for almost 40 years, from the
Apple II through the iMac.

23
00:01:18.106 --> 00:01:21.296 A:middle
We had a huge influx of
kids into the ecosystem

24
00:01:21.516 --> 00:01:24.796 A:middle
with the iPod, the most
popular music playback device

25
00:01:24.796 --> 00:01:26.046 A:middle
in the history of man.

26
00:01:26.666 --> 00:01:30.446 A:middle
And now we've got a huge
number of kids both in homes

27
00:01:30.446 --> 00:01:32.976 A:middle
and in the schools using
our mobile devices.

28
00:01:33.416 --> 00:01:36.216 A:middle
Now, it was great
when we started out,

29
00:01:36.216 --> 00:01:38.006 A:middle
because it was a
fairly simple model.

30
00:01:38.336 --> 00:01:40.876 A:middle
Parents would buy a device
that was pretty expensive.

31
00:01:41.226 --> 00:01:43.586 A:middle
They would buy some
software at a store.

32
00:01:43.906 --> 00:01:46.356 A:middle
They would put it
on their device,

33
00:01:46.416 --> 00:01:48.966 A:middle
and their kids would use it
in their home or classroom,

34
00:01:49.226 --> 00:01:52.216 A:middle
and that was pretty easy
and it was pretty safe,

35
00:01:52.336 --> 00:01:53.856 A:middle
but it's a different world now.

36
00:01:53.856 --> 00:01:57.416 A:middle
It's different for kids, and
it's different for parents, too.

37
00:01:58.176 --> 00:02:01.246 A:middle
Kids are beset by a
world on the Internet

38
00:02:01.246 --> 00:02:02.976 A:middle
where there are millions
of strangers

39
00:02:02.976 --> 00:02:05.806 A:middle
out there they can have
instantaneous contact with,

40
00:02:06.076 --> 00:02:08.406 A:middle
both other kids and grownups.

41
00:02:08.866 --> 00:02:11.936 A:middle
And there's also billions
of dollars of marketing

42
00:02:11.936 --> 00:02:16.236 A:middle
and merchandising that are aimed
at those kids, and that's why

43
00:02:16.236 --> 00:02:18.136 A:middle
around the world
people are working

44
00:02:18.166 --> 00:02:21.196 A:middle
on legislation to protect kids.

45
00:02:21.436 --> 00:02:24.926 A:middle
Now, we've been doing some
things gradually through OS X

46
00:02:24.956 --> 00:02:29.336 A:middle
and through iOS to give
parents and kids some protection

47
00:02:29.826 --> 00:02:31.356 A:middle
in the use of technology.

48
00:02:31.666 --> 00:02:35.396 A:middle
The parental controls that
have been in OS X forever

49
00:02:35.766 --> 00:02:43.976 A:middle
and the restrictions on iOS will
really help parents configure

50
00:02:43.976 --> 00:02:47.246 A:middle
the device to work the way they
want it to work with their kids,

51
00:02:47.246 --> 00:02:50.006 A:middle
and as app developers you're
kind of accustomed to this.

52
00:02:50.006 --> 00:02:52.286 A:middle
Sometimes, as in the
previous session,

53
00:02:52.506 --> 00:02:55.526 A:middle
when you go to use a
restricted data class,

54
00:02:55.956 --> 00:02:57.196 A:middle
it just won't be available,

55
00:02:57.196 --> 00:03:00.036 A:middle
because there's been a parental
control set on that device.

56
00:03:00.356 --> 00:03:03.446 A:middle
So, you're accustomed to dealing
with that as app developers.

57
00:03:04.226 --> 00:03:07.986 A:middle
And then when we start
putting networked capabilities

58
00:03:07.986 --> 00:03:13.066 A:middle
in the hands of users, we're
making some accommodations

59
00:03:13.096 --> 00:03:16.286 A:middle
to do things that are
specifically directed for kids,

60
00:03:16.576 --> 00:03:18.606 A:middle
Game Center for example.

61
00:03:18.816 --> 00:03:21.636 A:middle
We knew that a lot of kids
would be using Game Center

62
00:03:21.636 --> 00:03:22.946 A:middle
on their parent's devices,

63
00:03:23.236 --> 00:03:25.846 A:middle
and so we let them have
their own handles regardless

64
00:03:25.846 --> 00:03:26.506 A:middle
of their age.

65
00:03:26.786 --> 00:03:28.686 A:middle
They're more or less anonymous.

66
00:03:28.686 --> 00:03:31.036 A:middle
We don't collect
personal information.

67
00:03:31.356 --> 00:03:33.666 A:middle
We don't allow chat
for Game Center handles

68
00:03:33.666 --> 00:03:34.956 A:middle
for kids under 13.

69
00:03:35.136 --> 00:03:36.456 A:middle
There is no ads.

70
00:03:36.456 --> 00:03:37.856 A:middle
It's generic screen names.

71
00:03:37.856 --> 00:03:39.786 A:middle
There's no image sharing.

72
00:03:40.126 --> 00:03:43.066 A:middle
The chat messages they can
use are canned messages only,

73
00:03:43.066 --> 00:03:44.196 A:middle
not free-form chat.

74
00:03:44.546 --> 00:03:47.656 A:middle
So, we've created some, you
know, little cul-de-sacs

75
00:03:47.656 --> 00:03:50.486 A:middle
of functionality
for kids under 13.

76
00:03:53.196 --> 00:03:55.686 A:middle
There is a new kid's
category in the App Store

77
00:03:55.686 --> 00:03:56.666 A:middle
that you may have heard about.

78
00:03:56.666 --> 00:03:58.556 A:middle
You can go in the App
Store guidelines or go

79
00:03:58.556 --> 00:04:00.016 A:middle
to the App Store
sessions or labs

80
00:04:00.016 --> 00:04:01.506 A:middle
and learn a little
bit more about these.

81
00:04:01.876 --> 00:04:04.916 A:middle
If you're targeting your
apps to sell to the parents

82
00:04:05.226 --> 00:04:08.566 A:middle
of young kids who are going
to use them, there's a couple

83
00:04:08.566 --> 00:04:11.196 A:middle
of things you need to do
to get into that category.

84
00:04:11.566 --> 00:04:13.786 A:middle
You have to have a privacy
policy on your page,

85
00:04:13.786 --> 00:04:18.055 A:middle
and you've got to link to that
privacy policy on your app page.

86
00:04:18.386 --> 00:04:21.666 A:middle
You cannot have
behavioral-oriented advertising.

87
00:04:21.946 --> 00:04:23.566 A:middle
You can have contextual
advertising,

88
00:04:23.566 --> 00:04:25.586 A:middle
but not behavioral-oriented
advertising

89
00:04:25.826 --> 00:04:27.036 A:middle
that tracks your kid.

90
00:04:27.036 --> 00:04:31.606 A:middle
You can do no tracking
across sites or across apps.

91
00:04:31.606 --> 00:04:34.926 A:middle
The contextual ads must
be appropriate for kids,

92
00:04:35.336 --> 00:04:37.426 A:middle
and you've got to
have a parental gate

93
00:04:37.426 --> 00:04:40.146 A:middle
on your app before you
get out of the app to go

94
00:04:40.146 --> 00:04:44.846 A:middle
to In-App Purchases back to the
App Store or to any online site.

95
00:04:45.296 --> 00:04:48.146 A:middle
So again, little
cul-de-sacs of functionality

96
00:04:48.146 --> 00:04:50.776 A:middle
to accommodate kids
using our technology.

97
00:04:51.686 --> 00:04:56.046 A:middle
But there is a lot going on
in the world and a lot going

98
00:04:56.046 --> 00:05:00.676 A:middle
on in the United States about
what technology companies,

99
00:05:00.676 --> 00:05:03.516 A:middle
Internet companies in
general have to do about kids

100
00:05:03.806 --> 00:05:07.606 A:middle
to give parents the safety
and control they want.

101
00:05:07.606 --> 00:05:09.856 A:middle
Generally it's about
being sensitive

102
00:05:10.596 --> 00:05:12.556 A:middle
to the needs of parents
and kids.

103
00:05:13.066 --> 00:05:15.646 A:middle
But, some areas that
we've gotten scrutiny

104
00:05:15.646 --> 00:05:17.216 A:middle
and you may have
gotten scrutiny,

105
00:05:17.546 --> 00:05:21.596 A:middle
including not being clear
about the total cost of an app.

106
00:05:21.946 --> 00:05:24.496 A:middle
A free app that may
cost hundreds of dollars

107
00:05:24.496 --> 00:05:26.506 A:middle
in In-App Purchases in order

108
00:05:26.506 --> 00:05:30.136 A:middle
to have a good play
experience is going

109
00:05:30.136 --> 00:05:32.236 A:middle
to be considered a
little out of line.

110
00:05:32.336 --> 00:05:33.586 A:middle
You may need to look at that.

111
00:05:33.896 --> 00:05:36.186 A:middle
Aggressive exhortations to buy,

112
00:05:36.186 --> 00:05:39.226 A:middle
where you are constantly
bombarded with the urge

113
00:05:39.226 --> 00:05:42.246 A:middle
to spend money, that's not
going to be OK for some

114
00:05:42.246 --> 00:05:44.436 A:middle
of the regulatory
agencies, and you may have

115
00:05:44.436 --> 00:05:45.836 A:middle
to be careful about
some of these.

116
00:05:46.236 --> 00:05:49.086 A:middle
You're responsible for
local law compliance.

117
00:05:49.276 --> 00:05:51.546 A:middle
There are some principles
that you can follow.

118
00:05:51.546 --> 00:05:53.256 A:middle
The British government
has put some together.

119
00:05:53.256 --> 00:05:54.646 A:middle
There's a link on this website.

120
00:05:54.646 --> 00:05:56.246 A:middle
You can go back to
the tape and read it.

121
00:05:56.526 --> 00:05:58.936 A:middle
There's some general principles
about dealing with kids

122
00:05:59.186 --> 00:06:03.066 A:middle
in websites and in apps that are
really, really good to follow.

