148
00:07:00.216 --> 00:07:02.546 A:middle
The thing that's going
to affect you most

149
00:07:03.226 --> 00:07:07.176 A:middle
as developers is the Children's
Online Privacy Protection Act

150
00:07:07.856 --> 00:07:09.426 A:middle
of 2000, OK.

151
00:07:09.426 --> 00:07:12.756 A:middle
This was originally
written to focus

152
00:07:12.756 --> 00:07:15.356 A:middle
on websites and online services.

153
00:07:15.756 --> 00:07:19.106 A:middle
It applies to sites
that are directed at

154
00:07:19.786 --> 00:07:24.196 A:middle
or have actual knowledge of
use by kids under age 13,

155
00:07:24.506 --> 00:07:25.816 A:middle
and it restricts you

156
00:07:25.816 --> 00:07:28.086 A:middle
from collecting identifying
information

157
00:07:28.256 --> 00:07:29.936 A:middle
without parental consent.

158
00:07:30.256 --> 00:07:33.586 A:middle
Pretty straightforward as
it goes as it was in 2000,

159
00:07:33.586 --> 00:07:35.996 A:middle
but a lot has happened
since 2000.

160
00:07:36.316 --> 00:07:38.096 A:middle
The way the law was
originally written was

161
00:07:38.096 --> 00:07:40.246 A:middle
that you couldn't collect
the first or last name,

162
00:07:40.246 --> 00:07:43.836 A:middle
the email address or phone
number, any physical address,

163
00:07:43.836 --> 00:07:47.196 A:middle
street name or the name of a
city or a town, Social Security,

164
00:07:47.446 --> 00:07:50.986 A:middle
user identifier, any screen
name that would have a way

165
00:07:50.986 --> 00:07:55.206 A:middle
of contacting the kid, or
information that combines

166
00:07:55.206 --> 00:07:56.276 A:middle
with any of those above.

167
00:07:56.546 --> 00:07:59.556 A:middle
And it defined an
acceptable mechanism

168
00:07:59.836 --> 00:08:01.896 A:middle
to get parental consent.

169
00:08:01.896 --> 00:08:07.476 A:middle
Well, last year in 2013,
the Federal Trade Commission

170
00:08:07.476 --> 00:08:10.466 A:middle
in the United States revised
that act to clarify it,

171
00:08:10.636 --> 00:08:12.136 A:middle
expand it a little bit,

172
00:08:12.136 --> 00:08:14.896 A:middle
and these are the things you'll
really need to careful about.

173
00:08:15.276 --> 00:08:17.876 A:middle
They clarified that everything
that applied to websites

174
00:08:17.876 --> 00:08:19.676 A:middle
in 2000 applies to mobile, too.

175
00:08:19.816 --> 00:08:23.056 A:middle
So, all of your apps
are affected.

176
00:08:23.606 --> 00:08:26.016 A:middle
They expanded the definition
of personal information

177
00:08:26.016 --> 00:08:29.166 A:middle
that requires parental consent
according the new capabilities

178
00:08:29.446 --> 00:08:30.446 A:middle
of mobile devices.

179
00:08:30.866 --> 00:08:36.296 A:middle
So, any photo or video or sound
recording that your app makes

180
00:08:36.506 --> 00:08:41.606 A:middle
that could include the
child's own image is subject

181
00:08:41.716 --> 00:08:43.486 A:middle
to the COPPA regulations, OK,

182
00:08:43.756 --> 00:08:45.226 A:middle
very important for
you to know that.

183
00:08:45.626 --> 00:08:48.996 A:middle
Geolocation that can isolate
the kid's location to a city

184
00:08:48.996 --> 00:08:52.926 A:middle
or town - subject to COPPA
regulations, any screen name

185
00:08:52.926 --> 00:08:54.956 A:middle
or identifier that can
be used for contact,

186
00:08:54.956 --> 00:08:58.056 A:middle
that's pretty much the same,
or a persistent identifier

187
00:08:58.056 --> 00:09:00.746 A:middle
that identifies them
across sites or services.

188
00:09:00.746 --> 00:09:05.186 A:middle
If you're using this information
solely within your app

189
00:09:05.646 --> 00:09:07.806 A:middle
and solely for internal
functionality

190
00:09:07.806 --> 00:09:09.906 A:middle
to your app, that's OK.

191
00:09:10.366 --> 00:09:13.146 A:middle
But, if it goes up on a website,
if it goes outside your app,

192
00:09:13.146 --> 00:09:15.156 A:middle
if you're using it
for purposes other

193
00:09:15.156 --> 00:09:18.506 A:middle
than just making your app
work, then you're subject

194
00:09:18.506 --> 00:09:19.706 A:middle
to the requirements

195
00:09:19.706 --> 00:09:22.916 A:middle
of the Children's Online
Privacy Protection Act.

196
00:09:23.366 --> 00:09:27.866 A:middle
And there are some requirements
of that, and we're going

197
00:09:27.866 --> 00:09:29.176 A:middle
to go into that later.

198
00:09:29.876 --> 00:09:32.986 A:middle
Now, kids under 13
who are subject

199
00:09:32.986 --> 00:09:35.316 A:middle
to the COPPA law have Apple IDs.

200
00:09:35.586 --> 00:09:36.566 A:middle
They have it in two ways.

201
00:09:37.436 --> 00:09:39.746 A:middle
The first is an Apple
ID for Students Program,

202
00:09:39.986 --> 00:09:41.606 A:middle
and this is what we
rolled out last year.

203
00:09:42.166 --> 00:09:45.666 A:middle
It's a program that gets
verified parental consent

204
00:09:45.666 --> 00:09:48.466 A:middle
through the COPPA law
through schools, OK.

205
00:09:48.786 --> 00:09:51.266 A:middle
We've rolled it out in several
large school districts starting

206
00:09:51.266 --> 00:09:52.826 A:middle
last year and going
into this year,

207
00:09:53.066 --> 00:09:57.646 A:middle
and they're full-fledged Apple
IDs for iCloud and iTunes.

208
00:09:57.646 --> 00:09:59.926 A:middle
They're not these
Game Center accounts.

209
00:09:59.926 --> 00:10:01.016 A:middle
They're not kid accounts.

210
00:10:01.046 --> 00:10:02.076 A:middle
They're not junior accounts.

211
00:10:02.446 --> 00:10:03.956 A:middle
They really are full
accounts, OK.

212
00:10:04.786 --> 00:10:07.486 A:middle
There are a couple of little
things we've applied to them.

213
00:10:07.786 --> 00:10:10.566 A:middle
Students do not receive
marketing materials from Apple.

214
00:10:10.566 --> 00:10:12.476 A:middle
That box is implicitly checked

215
00:10:12.476 --> 00:10:14.026 A:middle
to not receive marketing
materials,

216
00:10:14.586 --> 00:10:17.686 A:middle
and the Limit Ad Tracking
switch is automatically set

217
00:10:17.686 --> 00:10:19.556 A:middle
for accounts for kids under 13.

218
00:10:19.816 --> 00:10:22.826 A:middle
Now, this is really
only for, you know,

219
00:10:22.826 --> 00:10:25.036 A:middle
a few tens of thousands
of kids now.

220
00:10:25.036 --> 00:10:26.416 A:middle
And of course, we're
going to expand

221
00:10:26.416 --> 00:10:28.436 A:middle
that in more school districts.

222
00:10:28.646 --> 00:10:31.326 A:middle
But, what we announced
Monday is much bigger,

223
00:10:31.736 --> 00:10:33.156 A:middle
and that's Family Sharing.

224
00:10:33.986 --> 00:10:38.376 A:middle
Family Sharing is a method to
get verifiable parental consent

225
00:10:38.506 --> 00:10:43.166 A:middle
under the COPPA law for any
family in the U.S., and in fact,

226
00:10:43.166 --> 00:10:47.236 A:middle
we're using the same
mechanism worldwide for parents

227
00:10:47.236 --> 00:10:50.206 A:middle
to create Apple IDs
for young kids.

228
00:10:50.786 --> 00:10:54.076 A:middle
It integrates with the Ask
To Buy feature that you saw

229
00:10:54.076 --> 00:10:57.776 A:middle
on Monday, so that
parents can see and approve

230
00:10:57.776 --> 00:10:59.666 A:middle
of purchases by their kids.

231
00:10:59.966 --> 00:11:01.826 A:middle
Once again, just
like the student IDs,

232
00:11:01.826 --> 00:11:05.666 A:middle
they're full-fledged Apple
IDs for iCloud and iTunes.

233
00:11:05.666 --> 00:11:08.706 A:middle
The same switches are set, no
marketing and no ad tracking,

234
00:11:09.316 --> 00:11:11.236 A:middle
and the verified
parental consent is set

235
00:11:11.236 --> 00:11:12.426 A:middle
up by a special mechanism.

236
00:11:12.426 --> 00:11:16.316 A:middle
So it's a way for us to get
the parents to create accounts

237
00:11:16.316 --> 00:11:20.146 A:middle
for kids under 13 and then
bring them into the family,

238
00:11:20.586 --> 00:11:22.346 A:middle
let them share existing
purchases

239
00:11:22.426 --> 00:11:23.546 A:middle
and make new purchases.

240
00:11:24.526 --> 00:11:25.916 A:middle
Let me walk you a little bit

241
00:11:25.916 --> 00:11:28.146 A:middle
through how the whole
Family Sharing program works

242
00:11:28.146 --> 00:11:29.886 A:middle
because that'll give you
a good background for it.

243
00:11:30.586 --> 00:11:33.906 A:middle
You start with the person
who has a payment method

244
00:11:34.556 --> 00:11:38.436 A:middle
and an Apple ID who decides
to be a family organizer.

245
00:11:38.596 --> 00:11:40.856 A:middle
And the family organizer can add

246
00:11:40.856 --> 00:11:45.576 A:middle
or invite other existing
accounts into the family

247
00:11:46.166 --> 00:11:47.726 A:middle
and share their payment method

248
00:11:48.116 --> 00:11:51.776 A:middle
and share their existing
purchases with them.

249
00:11:52.206 --> 00:11:55.986 A:middle
They can also create new
accounts for kids under 13

250
00:11:56.986 --> 00:11:58.276 A:middle
and create a family circle.

251
00:11:58.276 --> 00:12:00.676 A:middle
That can be up to
six accounts total.

252
00:12:00.966 --> 00:12:03.476 A:middle
And the requirement is
that during the life

253
00:12:03.476 --> 00:12:05.206 A:middle
of the family all
the accounts have

254
00:12:05.246 --> 00:12:08.656 A:middle
to use the family
organizer's payment method

255
00:12:08.656 --> 00:12:10.756 A:middle
or credit card, OK.

256
00:12:10.756 --> 00:12:14.696 A:middle
The way Purchase Sharing works
is that you have this bucket

257
00:12:14.696 --> 00:12:18.696 A:middle
of purchases that you've made,
and that is made available

258
00:12:19.236 --> 00:12:20.596 A:middle
to everybody in your family.

259
00:12:20.596 --> 00:12:24.596 A:middle
They can see all of your
movies, books and apps that -

260
00:12:24.596 --> 00:12:26.216 A:middle
and songs that you
have purchased.

261
00:12:26.766 --> 00:12:29.846 A:middle
They can pick one out of your
purchases and re-download it

262
00:12:29.876 --> 00:12:32.706 A:middle
to their device as if it was
in their purchase history.

263
00:12:32.916 --> 00:12:34.236 A:middle
It's not their title now.

264
00:12:34.236 --> 00:12:35.836 A:middle
It doesn't show up in
their purchase history.

265
00:12:36.096 --> 00:12:39.116 A:middle
It's still yours, and then
if you leave the family,

266
00:12:39.346 --> 00:12:41.056 A:middle
they lose the rights
to that title.

267
00:12:41.676 --> 00:12:45.126 A:middle
And then the Ask To Buy
capability is really cool.

268
00:12:45.496 --> 00:12:49.126 A:middle
If one of your family members
has the Ask To Buy switch turned

269
00:12:49.126 --> 00:12:51.566 A:middle
on and is shopping in any
of the stores and wants

270
00:12:51.566 --> 00:12:55.006 A:middle
to purchase something, at time

271
00:12:55.256 --> 00:12:59.406 A:middle
of purchase request a
notification is sent

272
00:12:59.706 --> 00:13:03.366 A:middle
to the organizer and other
parents in the family saying

273
00:13:03.536 --> 00:13:05.466 A:middle
that this person wants
to buy this product

274
00:13:05.466 --> 00:13:06.776 A:middle
with a link to the product page.

275
00:13:07.446 --> 00:13:09.126 A:middle
And the organizer
and the parents

276
00:13:09.126 --> 00:13:13.846 A:middle
or guardians get the option to
approve or deny that request.

277
00:13:15.196 --> 00:13:18.696 A:middle
And on approval, they
complete that purchase.

278
00:13:18.996 --> 00:13:22.486 A:middle
Now, this is going to affect the
way your In-App Purchases work,

279
00:13:22.486 --> 00:13:26.236 A:middle
because there may be a
long time between the time

280
00:13:26.236 --> 00:13:29.276 A:middle
when the user taps the
In-App Purchase Buy button

281
00:13:29.606 --> 00:13:33.396 A:middle
and when the parent
actually sees it, taps OK,

282
00:13:33.716 --> 00:13:35.706 A:middle
the request comes back
and they get to buy that.

283
00:13:36.086 --> 00:13:37.916 A:middle
Go back and look
at James Wilson's

284
00:13:37.986 --> 00:13:40.746 A:middle
"Optimizing StoreKit
Transaction" session.

285
00:13:41.066 --> 00:13:42.466 A:middle
There was one given yesterday

286
00:13:42.466 --> 00:13:44.076 A:middle
and he's reprising
it tomorrow morning.

287
00:13:44.446 --> 00:13:46.706 A:middle
See that. He's got some
great tips for how to deal

288
00:13:46.706 --> 00:13:49.486 A:middle
with that in your app.

289
00:13:49.746 --> 00:13:52.536 A:middle
So, given all of that,
what does this mean to you?

290
00:13:52.726 --> 00:13:55.206 A:middle
What does regulatory
environment mean to you?

291
00:13:55.206 --> 00:13:57.706 A:middle
What do the new under
13 accounts mean to you?

292
00:13:57.966 --> 00:14:01.606 A:middle
What is Ask To Buy and
Family Sharing mean to you?

293
00:14:02.326 --> 00:14:05.736 A:middle
And at this time
I want you to say-

294
00:14:06.116 --> 00:14:08.746 A:middle
&gt;&gt; [group response] I
want to call my lawyer.

295
00:14:08.746 --> 00:14:09.716 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Oh come on, come on, come on.

296
00:14:09.716 --> 00:14:10.366 A:middle
One, two, three.

297
00:14:10.586 --> 00:14:12.216 A:middle
&gt;&gt; [group response] I
want to call my lawyer.

298
00:14:12.216 --> 00:14:13.096 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Great. OK.

299
00:14:13.336 --> 00:14:17.096 A:middle
Only your lawyer can tell
you what this means to you

300
00:14:17.096 --> 00:14:19.536 A:middle
in the context of your
app and your company.

301
00:14:19.996 --> 00:14:21.626 A:middle
But, the thing you got
to know is that kids

302
00:14:21.626 --> 00:14:25.006 A:middle
under 13 may be buying,
selling, buying,

303
00:14:25.006 --> 00:14:26.896 A:middle
sharing and using your apps.

304
00:14:27.266 --> 00:14:32.106 A:middle
So, you've got to tell whether
your apps are directed at kids

305
00:14:32.106 --> 00:14:36.966 A:middle
under 13 or whether you have
specific knowledge that kids

306
00:14:36.966 --> 00:14:38.336 A:middle
under 13 are using your apps.

307
00:14:38.616 --> 00:14:42.176 A:middle
If you've got a general-purpose
app like a word processor

308
00:14:42.176 --> 00:14:45.526 A:middle
or a to-do list reminder,
you're not targeted at kids,

309
00:14:45.736 --> 00:14:47.946 A:middle
you're not in the kids
section of the store,

310
00:14:48.226 --> 00:14:52.206 A:middle
you don't ask their age
anywhere - you're probably OK

311
00:14:52.206 --> 00:14:55.616 A:middle
under the COPPA law, which only
affects things that are directed

312
00:14:55.616 --> 00:14:59.146 A:middle
at or you have actual
knowledge of the user's age.

313
00:14:59.406 --> 00:15:01.936 A:middle
Again, you have to consult
your lawyer in order

314
00:15:01.936 --> 00:15:05.006 A:middle
to know whether you do or do
not follow- fall under the law.

315
00:15:05.466 --> 00:15:07.886 A:middle
But, typically, if you
have a general-purpose app,

316
00:15:08.256 --> 00:15:10.776 A:middle
you don't market to kids,
you're not in the kids section,

317
00:15:11.016 --> 00:15:14.196 A:middle
you don't know the age,
then you don't have to worry

318
00:15:14.196 --> 00:15:16.676 A:middle
about COPPA conformance
specifically.

319
00:15:18.066 --> 00:15:22.056 A:middle
But, if your app is directed
at kids, which it probably is

320
00:15:22.056 --> 00:15:26.246 A:middle
if you're in this room, you
have some implementation choices

321
00:15:26.596 --> 00:15:30.756 A:middle
to either avoid requirements
for conformance with COPPA

322
00:15:31.046 --> 00:15:33.156 A:middle
or to conform with
the COPPA law.

323
00:15:33.346 --> 00:15:35.126 A:middle
And there three basic
approaches, and I'm going

324
00:15:35.126 --> 00:15:36.316 A:middle
to walk you through them now.

325
00:15:36.796 --> 00:15:39.416 A:middle
You can either avoid
doing the things

326
00:15:39.416 --> 00:15:41.106 A:middle
that subject you to
COPPA regulation.

327
00:15:41.276 --> 00:15:42.236 A:middle
Just stay out of it.

328
00:15:42.396 --> 00:15:44.646 A:middle
Do not collect personally
identifying information -

329
00:15:44.736 --> 00:15:45.656 A:middle
it's a great alternative.

330
00:15:46.646 --> 00:15:49.436 A:middle
Or you can choose to
collect the information

331
00:15:49.436 --> 00:15:53.536 A:middle
of how old the user is and
present a forked experience,

332
00:15:53.536 --> 00:15:56.766 A:middle
different experiences for
kids over 13 and under 13,

333
00:15:57.206 --> 00:16:01.716 A:middle
disable the personally
identifying information

334
00:16:01.716 --> 00:16:03.756 A:middle
experience for the
kids under 13.

335
00:16:04.116 --> 00:16:05.896 A:middle
That's a viable choice.

336
00:16:05.966 --> 00:16:07.346 A:middle
That's a good choice
for you to make.

337
00:16:08.066 --> 00:16:13.326 A:middle
Or, you can, if you're all about
that information, if you're all

338
00:16:13.326 --> 00:16:15.536 A:middle
about video, if you're all
about chat, if you're all

339
00:16:15.536 --> 00:16:19.836 A:middle
about sharing stuff, you really
need to address kids under 13

340
00:16:19.936 --> 00:16:23.236 A:middle
with the full features of your
application, then you have

341
00:16:23.306 --> 00:16:27.046 A:middle
to get verifiable parental
consent of the use -

342
00:16:27.236 --> 00:16:30.796 A:middle
from the user's parents before
you can proceed with the app,

343
00:16:30.796 --> 00:16:32.716 A:middle
and we'll lead you through
some steps to do that.

344
00:16:34.996 --> 00:16:39.146 A:middle
So, let's look at the first
alternative, avoid it.

345
00:16:40.106 --> 00:16:42.996 A:middle
This is pretty easy
for most apps.

346
00:16:43.606 --> 00:16:45.836 A:middle
Don't collect personally
identifying information.

347
00:16:46.506 --> 00:16:48.476 A:middle
Don't show behaviorally
targeted ads,

348
00:16:48.476 --> 00:16:49.886 A:middle
although contextual
ads are fine.

349
00:16:50.356 --> 00:16:52.006 A:middle
Don't support photos.

350
00:16:52.706 --> 00:16:54.426 A:middle
Don't support voice recording.

351
00:16:54.836 --> 00:16:56.526 A:middle
Don't support social networking.

352
00:16:56.986 --> 00:16:59.136 A:middle
Don't support finding
your location.

353
00:16:59.886 --> 00:17:02.216 A:middle
Don't support your
own push notifications

354
00:17:02.546 --> 00:17:04.646 A:middle
or any other COPPA-regulated
functionality.

355
00:17:05.026 --> 00:17:07.506 A:middle
You can go a long way
actually without doing those

356
00:17:07.506 --> 00:17:09.846 A:middle
if that's what your app is
about, if it's a simple game

357
00:17:09.846 --> 00:17:11.486 A:middle
or a general purpose
application.

358
00:17:12.675 --> 00:17:15.796 A:middle
Ask To Buy does not make
you COPPA compliant.

359
00:17:15.796 --> 00:17:18.006 A:middle
Getting the parental
permission to purchase

360
00:17:18.006 --> 00:17:22.066 A:middle
and download the game is
not COPPA compliant parental

361
00:17:22.066 --> 00:17:23.796 A:middle
notification and consent

362
00:17:24.126 --> 00:17:26.246 A:middle
to collect personally
identifying information.

363
00:17:26.636 --> 00:17:29.186 A:middle
So, just because the kid bought
your game through Ask To Buy,

364
00:17:29.426 --> 00:17:30.726 A:middle
that doesn't let
you off the hook.

365
00:17:30.966 --> 00:17:34.346 A:middle
If you limit yourself to
what Game Center does,

366
00:17:34.346 --> 00:17:37.666 A:middle
you're generally good, but
you got to check your app

367
00:17:37.666 --> 00:17:40.216 A:middle
and make sure that you're not
doing any of these things.

368
00:17:40.316 --> 00:17:44.936 A:middle
If you saw the previous
presentation, then you know

369
00:17:44.936 --> 00:17:47.426 A:middle
that there are some
protected data classes

370
00:17:47.596 --> 00:17:50.196 A:middle
in both platforms, iOS and OS X.

371
00:17:50.696 --> 00:17:52.836 A:middle
If you look at those
protected data classes,

372
00:17:53.246 --> 00:17:56.166 A:middle
this gives you a really good
idea of whether you're going

373
00:17:56.166 --> 00:17:58.346 A:middle
to be generally compliant
with COPPA or not.

374
00:17:58.576 --> 00:18:03.866 A:middle
If you're using location or
contacts or photos or microphone

375
00:18:04.106 --> 00:18:08.416 A:middle
or the worldwide or the
camera or social or HealthKit,

376
00:18:09.226 --> 00:18:12.326 A:middle
you are subject to COPPA
regulations, and you need

377
00:18:12.326 --> 00:18:13.166 A:middle
to be careful about that.

378
00:18:13.166 --> 00:18:15.576 A:middle
Even Bluetooth, because
Bluetooth has a persistent

379
00:18:15.576 --> 00:18:18.976 A:middle
identifier that can be
tracked across devices

380
00:18:18.976 --> 00:18:21.706 A:middle
and across locales,
and so even use

381
00:18:21.706 --> 00:18:23.626 A:middle
of Bluetooth makes
you subject to COPPA.

382
00:18:24.156 --> 00:18:27.266 A:middle
So, let me show you some demos

383
00:18:27.686 --> 00:18:32.946 A:middle
of some applications
that are PII-free.

384
00:18:34.406 --> 00:18:40.916 A:middle
This one is called
"Bonsai Slice."

385
00:18:41.676 --> 00:18:45.716 A:middle
It's a game where you
swack things with swords.

386
00:18:46.116 --> 00:18:47.576 A:middle
Again, you start it up.

387
00:18:48.226 --> 00:18:51.306 A:middle
There's not much to do
except tap to begin.

388
00:18:52.926 --> 00:18:57.016 A:middle
There's no particular login
or identification of yourself

389
00:18:57.016 --> 00:19:00.976 A:middle
or any setup, and you can just
go right into playing the game.

390
00:19:01.516 --> 00:19:06.046 A:middle
[ Game sounds ]

391
00:19:06.546 --> 00:19:08.926 A:middle
So, there we go.

392
00:19:08.926 --> 00:19:16.276 A:middle
I think that's enough
game demo for that.

393
00:19:17.546 --> 00:19:19.446 A:middle
So, that is the first approach,

394
00:19:19.446 --> 00:19:22.306 A:middle
which is just don't do
it and you'll be fine.

395
00:19:22.306 --> 00:19:24.056 A:middle
So, if you've got a
general purpose app

396
00:19:24.056 --> 00:19:25.666 A:middle
or you've got a kid oriented app

397
00:19:26.236 --> 00:19:28.316 A:middle
that doesn't collect any
personally identifying

398
00:19:28.316 --> 00:19:29.746 A:middle
information, you're fine.

399
00:19:29.746 --> 00:19:30.316 A:middle
You're in the clear.

400
00:19:31.946 --> 00:19:35.006 A:middle
The second approach is
to have an age screen

401
00:19:35.176 --> 00:19:38.356 A:middle
so you can tell whether
your user is under 13.

402
00:19:38.766 --> 00:19:42.356 A:middle
And then if they're over 13 you
can collect PII, and if they're

403
00:19:42.356 --> 00:19:45.996 A:middle
under 13 you just turn
off those features, OK.

404
00:19:46.376 --> 00:19:48.536 A:middle
It's pretty straightforward
to do.

405
00:19:49.166 --> 00:19:50.906 A:middle
One of the interesting
things is, well,

406
00:19:50.906 --> 00:19:53.316 A:middle
isn't their age personally
identifying information?

407
00:19:53.316 --> 00:19:54.676 A:middle
And the answer is no.

408
00:19:54.816 --> 00:19:55.256 A:middle
That's not.

409
00:19:55.346 --> 00:19:58.316 A:middle
You can ask their age, and
you can record their age

410
00:19:58.486 --> 00:19:59.956 A:middle
so you don't have
to ask every time.

411
00:20:00.046 --> 00:20:03.656 A:middle
If fact, we recommend that
what you do is you ask

412
00:20:03.656 --> 00:20:04.596 A:middle
on first launch.

413
00:20:05.196 --> 00:20:07.036 A:middle
You record the age

414
00:20:07.086 --> 00:20:11.466 A:middle
in per account iCloud
preferences store.

415
00:20:11.756 --> 00:20:14.036 A:middle
And so when that user
is logged into iCloud,

416
00:20:14.106 --> 00:20:17.586 A:middle
because your under-13 users are
all going to be iCloud users.

417
00:20:18.246 --> 00:20:22.816 A:middle
Anytime your app launches and
you read that recorded age

418
00:20:22.816 --> 00:20:26.606 A:middle
of over or under 13 from their
per app iCloud preferences,

419
00:20:26.936 --> 00:20:29.366 A:middle
you know whether this
user's under 13 or not,

420
00:20:29.366 --> 00:20:31.716 A:middle
and you don't have to ask
again, and you can continue

421
00:20:31.716 --> 00:20:32.726 A:middle
to tailor the preference -

422
00:20:32.926 --> 00:20:34.896 A:middle
continue to tailor
the experience

423
00:20:34.896 --> 00:20:36.746 A:middle
for that under-13 user.

424
00:20:37.086 --> 00:20:42.156 A:middle
If they're under 13,
you can't just exit.

425
00:20:42.546 --> 00:20:44.256 A:middle
That's not appropriate.

426
00:20:44.626 --> 00:20:47.536 A:middle
That is, have an app that
people can buy or download

427
00:20:47.866 --> 00:20:49.426 A:middle
and then have them
input their age

428
00:20:49.426 --> 00:20:51.156 A:middle
and then tell them,
oh you're too young.

429
00:20:51.386 --> 00:20:53.786 A:middle
Your app will be rejected
from the store if you do that.

430
00:20:54.466 --> 00:20:57.236 A:middle
If you have an age gate and
you have different behaviors

431
00:20:57.236 --> 00:20:59.636 A:middle
for above and under 13, you have

432
00:20:59.636 --> 00:21:04.176 A:middle
to have a pretty unified
valuable experience

433
00:21:04.176 --> 00:21:05.006 A:middle
for under 13.

434
00:21:05.006 --> 00:21:07.196 A:middle
You can't just quit, and
you can't have a really,

435
00:21:07.196 --> 00:21:08.696 A:middle
really crippled version
of the app.

436
00:21:08.696 --> 00:21:09.676 A:middle
It's got to be useful.

437
00:21:09.676 --> 00:21:10.446 A:middle
It's got to be fun.

438
00:21:10.956 --> 00:21:13.056 A:middle
But, you can omit
certain features like,

439
00:21:13.426 --> 00:21:15.346 A:middle
you know, like chat.

440
00:21:15.726 --> 00:21:18.746 A:middle
You can have chat in the over
13 and not have chat in the

441
00:21:18.746 --> 00:21:22.366 A:middle
under 13 as part of your
gameplay, for example.

442
00:21:22.366 --> 00:21:25.506 A:middle
Once again, you should be
thinking one, two, three.

443
00:21:25.866 --> 00:21:27.106 A:middle
&gt;&gt; [group response] I
want to call my lawyer.

444
00:21:27.346 --> 00:21:28.206 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Great, thank you.

445
00:21:28.606 --> 00:21:31.816 A:middle
And you might want to
have a parental gate too.

446
00:21:31.816 --> 00:21:34.386 A:middle
Parental gates are something
we recommend for applications

447
00:21:34.386 --> 00:21:37.846 A:middle
that are in the kids store,
where, you know, there is the

448
00:21:37.876 --> 00:21:39.646 A:middle
under 13s, where you
got to do one thing.

449
00:21:39.986 --> 00:21:43.046 A:middle
There's 13 through,
